----------------------------------------------------------------
3. DATA MODEL (models.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
@dataclass
class Invoice:
    file_path: str
    file_name: str
 
    # Extracted fields
    supplier_name: str
    supplier_cui: str
    supplier_iban: str
 
    invoice_number: str
    issue_date: date
    due_date: date
 
    subtotal: float
    vat_amount: float
    vat_rate: float
    total: float
    currency: str
 
    category: str                     (auto-classified)
    line_items: list[LineItem]
 
    # Quality fields
    confidence_score: float           (0.0 - 1.0)
    is_scanned: bool
    is_duplicate: bool
    is_outlier: bool
    is_near_due: bool
    parse_errors: list[str]
 
    processed_at: datetime
 
@dataclass
class LineItem:
    description: str
    quantity: float
    unit_price: float
    total: float
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
4. CORE — EXTRACTOR (extractor.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
FUNCTION: extract_invoice(file_path: str) -> Invoice
 
LOGIC:
  1. Open PDF with pdfplumber
  2. Check if text-extractable:
     - YES → extract text directly per page
     - NO  → flag as scanned → send to ocr.py
  3. Concatenate all page text
  4. Send raw text to parser.py
  5. Return populated Invoice object
 
HANDLES:
  - Multi-page invoices
  - Password-protected PDFs (skip + error log)
  - Corrupted PDFs (skip + error log)
  - Empty PDFs (skip + error log)
 
PARALLEL PROCESSING:
  - concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor
  - Max workers: CPU count - 1
  - Progress callback per file completed
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
5. CORE — OCR (ocr.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
FUNCTION: ocr_pdf(file_path: str) -> str
 
LOGIC:
  1. Convert PDF pages to images (pdf2image / Pillow)
  2. Preprocess image:
     - Grayscale
     - Denoise
     - Deskew
     - Increase contrast
  3. Run pytesseract with lang=ron+eng
  4. Return concatenated text
 
REQUIREMENTS:
  - Tesseract OCR installed (Windows .exe)
  - Romanian + English language packs
  - tesseract path auto-detected from Windows registry
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
6. CORE — PARSER (parser.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
FUNCTION: parse_fields(raw_text: str) -> dict
 
FIELDS EXTRACTED:
 
  supplier_name:
    - Regex patterns for Romanian invoice format
    - "Furnizor:", "Emitent:", "S.C.", "S.R.L.", "S.A."
    - Fallback: first capitalized multi-word on page 1
 
  supplier_cui:
    - Pattern: "CUI" or "CIF" followed by RO + 8-10 digits
 
  supplier_iban:
    - Pattern: IBAN format RO + 22 chars
 
  invoice_number:
    - Pattern: "Factura nr.", "Invoice No.", "Nr. factura"
    - Followed by alphanumeric sequence
 
  issue_date:
    - Multiple date formats: DD.MM.YYYY, DD/MM/YYYY, YYYY-MM-DD
    - Keywords: "Data:", "Emisa la:", "Issue date:"
 
  due_date:
    - Keywords: "Scadenta:", "Termen plata:", "Due date:"
 
  subtotal:
    - Keywords: "Subtotal", "Baza impozabila", "Net amount"
 
  vat_rate + vat_amount:
    - Pattern: "TVA 19%", "VAT 20%", followed by amount
 
  total:
    - Keywords: "Total de plata", "Total amount", "TOTAL"
    - Largest monetary value as fallback
 
  currency:
    - Pattern: RON, EUR, USD, GBP symbols or text
    - Default: RON if not found
 
  line_items:
    - Table detection via pdfplumber table extractor
    - Columns: description, qty, unit price, total
 
CONFIDENCE SCORING:
  - Each field scores 0 or 1 based on extraction success
  - Overall confidence = fields_extracted / total_fields
  - Score < 0.6 → flag for manual review
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
7. CORE — CLASSIFIER (classifier.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
FUNCTION: classify_invoice(invoice: Invoice) -> str
 
CATEGORIES:
  - Utilities      (keywords: curent, gaz, apa, energie, EON, E.ON, Electrica)
  - Software       (keywords: license, subscription, SaaS, software)
  - Services       (keywords: consultanta, servicii, prestari)
  - Products       (keywords: produse, marfuri, bunuri)
  - Transport      (keywords: transport, curierat, livrare, DHL, FanCourier)
  - Marketing      (keywords: publicitate, reclama, marketing, Google, Meta)
  - Office         (keywords: birotica, papetarie, consumabile)
  - Other          (fallback)
 
LOGIC:
  - Keyword matching on supplier_name + line_items descriptions
  - Returns highest-confidence category match
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
8. CORE — WATCHER (watcher.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
FUNCTION: start_watching(folder_path: str, callback: callable)
 
LOGIC:
  - watchdog FileSystemEventHandler
  - Monitors for .pdf file creation / modification
  - Debounce: 2 seconds (avoid partial file reads)
  - On new PDF detected → callback(file_path)
  - Runs in background thread
  - Stop/start via UI toggle
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
9. DATA — VALIDATOR (validator.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
DUPLICATE DETECTION:
  - Check invoice_number + supplier_cui combination
  - If match found → flag is_duplicate = True
  - Warning shown in UI + log
 
OUTLIER DETECTION:
  - Calculate mean + std dev of all invoice totals
  - Flag if total > mean + (2 * std_dev)
  - Configurable threshold in settings
 
DUE DATE ALERTING:
  - Flag if due_date within next N days (default: 7)
  - Configurable in settings
 
----------------------------------------------------------------
10. DATA — PROCESSOR (processor.py)
----------------------------------------------------------------
 
InvoiceDataFrame: pandas DataFrame wrapper
 
METHODS:
  add_invoice(invoice)
  remove_invoice(file_path)
  get_all() -> DataFrame
  filter_by_date(start, end) -> DataFrame
  filter_by_supplier(name) -> DataFrame
  filter_by_category(cat) -> DataFrame
  filter_by_flags(duplicates, outliers, near_due) -> DataFrame
  search(query: str) -> DataFrame           (searches all text fields)
  get_summary() -> dict:
    - total_invoices
    - total_value
    - total_vat
    - per_supplier (top 10)
    - per_category
    - per_month
    - flagged_count
